                                  and Agri-Food Canada. 1996</em>. ) </td>
                              </tr>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                        <div align="center"></div>
                        <p>&nbsp;</p>
                        <p align="left">(3) <em><b>Cryosol</b></em> -
                          is a high latitudes soil common in the tundra. This
                          soil has a layer of <b><a href="../physgeoglos/p.html#permafrost">permafrost</a></b> within
                          one meter of the soil surface. The image on the left
                          is of tundra landscape dominated by moss and lichen
                          vegetation. The soil profile has a permanently frozen
                          ice wedge beneath its surface.</p>
                        <p align=CENTER>
